MARKED FOR DEATH
Math Design Document
Based on Wild Bandito Mathematical Structure

Document Version: 0.7
Date: 2026-06-28
Status: Detailed Production Design
Target RTP: 96.73%
Grid: 5 Reels x 4 Rows (1024 Ways)
Max Win: 25,000x
Volatility: Medium (session) / High Ceiling

Design Philosophy
Replicate the core mathematical satisfaction of Wild Bandito (persistent multiplier growth + Marked symbol conversion to Wilds) while adapting the theme to a high-tension assassin / death fantasy. Wins fuel the multiplier. The multiplier fuels bigger wins. Marked targets become unstoppable Wilds as the death toll rises.

Revised & expanded for precision, completeness, and certifiable implementation.

1. GAME OVERVIEW & TARGETS

1.1 Key Parameters
Parameter | Target Value | Notes
RTP (Overall) | 96.73% | Matches Wild Bandito certified RTP
Session Volatility | Medium | Strong base engagement + high bonus ceiling
Max Win (Advertised) | 25,000x | High-end potential for marketing
Grid | 5 x 4 | 1024 Ways (left-to-right adjacent)
Hit Rate (Overall) | 28.7 - 29.0% | Target similar to source
~68 - 70% Primary session engagement driver
~26 - 28% High volatility segment
Base Game RTP
Free Spins RTP

1.2 Design Philosophy
Marked for Death delivers the same satisfying core loop that made Wild Bandito successful: wins create Marked conversions to Wilds, which enable more wins, which grow a persistent multiplier. The multiplier makes every small win meaningful because it amplifies future cascades within the spin (and the entire bonus round). The assassin theme reinforces the fantasy: 'Marked' symbols are targets that, once hit, become lethal Wild assassins themselves.

1.3 Design Goals
- Faithfully replicate the proven Wild Bandito math skeleton (cascades + Marked-to-Wild conversion + growing multiplier).
- Create strong tension and 'one more spin' engagement through persistent multiplier growth.
- Make Free Spins dramatically powerful via a guaranteed full Marked reel on reel 3 + non-resetting multiplier.
- Maintain medium base volatility with explosive bonus potential (25,000x ceiling).
- Keep all rules clean, unambiguous, and straightforward to certify and simulate.
- Provide a solid foundation for future differentiators (e.g. Giant Wild Banner / Execution feature).

